Annie found research showing that "no-rules parenting" (permissive parenting) can lead to:

- Poor self-regulation
- Difficulty with boundaries
- Increased behavioral problems
- Lower academic achievement
- Higher rates of anxiety

**Evidence suggests structured, positive approaches work better than either permissive or purely punitive methods.**
